			</p>

<!-- div attr= class="tasks"-->
			<p>
				(1) zero, there is . positive, there are . negative, there are .
			</p><!--</div attr= class="tasks">--><!--</div attr= class="ColoredDefinition">-->

<!-- div attr= class="objectivebox"-->
			<p>
				Using the discriminant to determine nature of solutions The discriminant is a number associated with quadratic equations, which tells us the number and type of solutions to the equation.
			</p><!--</div attr= class="objectivebox">-->

<!-- div attr= class="example"-->
			<p>
				<term>Example 1.1</term>.  <em>Use the discriminant to determine the number and type of solutions for each equation.</em>
			</p><!--</div attr= class="example">-->

<!-- div attr= class="tasks"-->
			<p>
				(1) <m>5x^{2}-3x+1=0</m> <m>2x^{2}=3-6x</m> <m>4x^{2}+12x=-9</m>
			</p><!--</div attr= class="tasks">-->

			<p>
				<term>Students - Check your understanding</term>
			</p>

<!-- div attr= class="checkyourunderstanding"-->
			<p>
				<term>CYU 1.4</term>.  <em>Solve the following equations.</em>
			</p><!--</div attr= class="checkyourunderstanding">-->

<!-- div attr= class="tasks"-->
			<p>
				(1) <m>\frac{3}{10}x^{2}-\frac{2}{5}x+\frac{7}{10}=0</m> <m>x^4 - 5x^2 + 6 = 0</m>.
			</p><!--</div attr= class="tasks">-->

<!-- div attr= class="checkyourunderstanding"-->
			<p>
				<term>CYU 1.5</term>.  <em>Find the discriminant and give the number and type of solution(s) of the quadratic equation <m>2x^2-3x+7=0</m>.</em>
			</p><!--</div attr= class="checkyourunderstanding">-->
